/*
** tests/diff_conflicts_fixtures/swap_conflicts_ext.lime -- v0.4.3
** Extension over conflicting_base.lime that BOTH resolves the
** STAR shift/reduce (via %left STAR) AND introduces a NEW
** DIV shift/reduce (DIV declared without precedence).
**
** Used by reverse-validation: with the symbolic-key code working,
** the diff reports 1 RESOLVED (STAR) + 1 NEW (DIV).  With a
** stubbed key (everything collapses to one bucket), the diff
** would incorrectly bucket the STAR-A and DIV-B as UNCHANGED.
** The two outcomes have visibly different summary lines.
*/

%left STAR.

%token DIV.

expr(R) ::= expr(L) DIV expr(M).  { R = L / M; }
